Package mmj.gmff

Class MinProofWorksheet

java.lang.Object
mmj.gmff.MinProofWorksheet
public class MinProofWorksheet extends Object
MinProofWorksheet is a minimalist ProofWorksheet containing just enough parsed proof data to generate a Model A type export file via GMFF.

Initially, GMFF Model A (export type) is supported but additional Models could be supported. Some Models might require the "Full Monte" -- our old friend ProofWorksheet, which requires full structural validation edits for loading.

  • Method Details

    • load

      public void load(String proofText)
      Loads the Proof Worksheet text into the MinProofWorksheet.
      Does the following:
      • Uses Java's readLine() to break the proofText into lines and strip off newline characters.
      • Each line is "tokenized" into strings containing either Metamath whitespace or a single Metamath token Strings, and the collection of Strings for each line is stored in an ArrayList
      • A non-blank character in a line's first column indicates a new ProofWorksheet statement and triggers loading of the previous MinProofWorkStmt. (Blank in column one indicates a continuation of the previous statement.)
      • The start of the first line of a ProofWorksheet statement is used to determine the type of statement to be loaded, and the appropriate constructor is invoked via MinProofWorkStmt.constructStmt().
      • A severe error anywhere causes structuralErrors to be set to true, and corresponding error message(s) stored in messages.
      Parameters:
      proofText - String data holding Proof Worksheet text.
